The article highlights the consensus among Cabinet Secretaries, Members of Congress, and State officials on the need to invest in rebuilding and reinvesting in the nation's infrastructure. Secretary of Transportation Elaine Chao emphasizes the reduction of red tape in infrastructure projects, while Secretary of the Interior Ryan Zinke discusses the neglected state of roads, bridges, and public lands. EPA Administrator Scott Pruitt emphasizes the role of the EPA in permitting reforms and localized investments. Various politicians, including Governor Pete Ricketts, Senator John Barrasso, Senator Jim Inhofe, Senator Dan Sullivan, Chairman Bill Shuster, Chairman Greg Walden, Chairman Rob Bishop, and Representative Marsha Blackburn, express their support for infrastructure investment and the need for permitting reforms and bipartisan cooperation.